        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-03-09T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-03-09T04:00:00-05:00" n="346" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d346">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">894A.00/3–947: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-03-09T17:00:00+08:00">March 9, 1947—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received March 9—5:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>500. Special representative Gimo departed Nanking this morning by air for Taipei.
                    (Reference Embassy’s telegram 499, March 9.) Colonel F. J. Dau, Assistant
                    Military Attaché, acting as Embassy courier, proceeded on same aircraft to
                    observe situation.</p>
                <p>Press currently reporting impending relief of General Chen Yi as Governor of
                    Taiwan.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
